Goodness.

385
00:26:30,667 --> 00:26:33,034
-Here is your popcorn.
-Sir, this isn't stopping.

386
00:26:35,300 --> 00:26:36,400
It stopped!

387
00:26:42,167 --> 00:26:44,968
-Sweet and refreshing coke.
-Thank you.

388
00:26:46,634 --> 00:26:47,767
Give it to me.

389
00:26:52,634 --> 00:26:53,901
Jae Min, stand by.

390
00:26:55,467 --> 00:26:57,500
Aren't those employees so weird?

391
00:26:58,367 --> 00:27:00,168
His voice sounded just like Yeong Sik.

392
00:27:01,334 --> 00:27:04,302
No way. Let's just go in
and watch the movie.

393
00:27:07,234 --> 00:27:10,468
Wow! You two look great together.

394
00:27:10,934 --> 00:27:14,334
I hope you lovebirds enjoy your movie...

395
00:27:14,968 --> 00:27:16,068
...and have a great time.

396
00:27:17,701 --> 00:27:19,535
-Did you wash your hair?
-Sorry?

397
00:27:21,267 --> 00:27:23,446
Let's go and watch the movie. Let's go in.

398
00:27:23,534 --> 00:27:24,634
Shall we?

399
00:27:25,767 --> 00:27:26,800
You're dead.

400
00:27:32,267 --> 00:27:33,434
Give me your bag.

401
00:27:35,934 --> 00:27:38,768
But why aren't there...

402
00:27:39,167 --> 00:27:40,501
...any people in here?

403
00:27:41,033 --> 00:27:43,934
Oh, I heard there was a group reservation,

404
00:27:44,267 --> 00:27:46,868
but it was canceled.
I guess that's why it's empty.

405
00:28:52,200 --> 00:28:53,600
Did you enjoy the movie?

406
00:28:53,834 --> 00:28:55,401
I loved the big screen.

407
00:28:56,367 --> 00:28:59,301
It felt so nice to be with
you at the movie theater.

408
00:28:59,901 --> 00:29:01,735
Do you want to go watch
baseball next time?

409
00:29:02,000 --> 00:29:03,834
I heard there are many concerts lately.

410
00:29:04,667 --> 00:29:05,800
How about a concert?

411
00:29:09,367 --> 00:29:10,834
A concert?

412
00:29:12,033 --> 00:29:14,834
Why? Is a concert too much?

413
00:29:17,567 --> 00:29:18,700
Of course not.

414
00:29:19,200 --> 00:29:22,212
If you want to go, just ask me.

415
00:29:22,300 --> 00:29:24,801
If you ask, of course...

416
00:29:25,667 --> 00:29:26,934
...we can go.

417
00:29:30,367 --> 00:29:31,868
Thank you for today.

418
00:29:33,267 --> 00:29:34,868
It must've been tough
for all the other guys.

419
00:29:36,567 --> 00:29:37,634
What do you mean?

420
00:29:39,567 --> 00:29:42,767
You don't have to try so hard for me.

421
00:29:44,634 --> 00:29:46,468
You don't have to rent
the whole theater...

422
00:29:46,767 --> 00:29:48,334
...and clean it up like that.

423
00:29:51,067 --> 00:29:52,167
You knew?

424
00:29:53,200 --> 00:29:55,500
That place was totally empty on a weekend.

425
00:29:55,968 --> 00:29:57,669
I'd be stupid not to know.

426
00:29:59,334 --> 00:30:00,935
And the smell of that disinfectant.

427
00:30:01,667 --> 00:30:03,601
I'm very familiar with it too, you know.

428
00:30:07,395 --> 00:30:09,329
I'm sorry. I just...

429
00:30:09,772 --> 00:30:12,706
...wanted to enjoy
an ordinary date with you.

430
00:30:13,067 --> 00:30:16,401
Instead of eating and
watching movies at home,

431
00:30:18,200 --> 00:30:20,467
I wanted to hold hands like this,
take walks together,

432
00:30:20,901 --> 00:30:22,135
and go to the movie theater.

433
00:30:34,634 --> 00:30:35,834
You're...

434
00:30:36,734 --> 00:30:38,101
...going through a lot because of me.

435
00:30:38,534 --> 00:30:40,301
Don't say that.

436
00:30:41,467 --> 00:30:43,880
The fact that I have you
by my side like this...

437
00:30:43,968 --> 00:30:45,368
...makes me so happy.

438
00:30:53,667 --> 00:30:56,001
My gosh, how romantic.

439
00:30:56,100 --> 00:30:58,334
You rented the entire theater
for your date?

440
00:30:58,601 --> 00:31:01,068
I thought things like that
only happened in movies.

441
00:31:01,434 --> 00:31:02,646
Stop making fun of me.

442
00:31:02,734 --> 00:31:04,146
I'm not in the mood for this.

443
00:31:04,234 --> 00:31:05,434
I'm not making fun of you.

444
00:31:06,133 --> 00:31:07,634
I'm truly impressed.

445
00:31:08,400 --> 00:31:09,734
But...

446
00:31:09,968 --> 00:31:13,502
...I wonder what's gotten into you...

447
00:31:13,901 --> 00:31:15,802
...for you to reach out to me first.

448
00:31:16,234 --> 00:31:19,168
And you even gave me this delicious tea.

449
00:31:20,534 --> 00:31:23,268
Well, nothing really.

450
00:31:25,634 --> 00:31:26,934
It's about my mysophobia.

451
00:31:27,434 --> 00:31:28,834
Aren't you going to treat it?

452
00:31:29,300 --> 00:31:31,467
I heard you're quite famous in the field.

453
00:31:33,801 --> 00:31:36,402
That was a model answer. Impressive.

454
00:31:36,634 --> 00:31:38,068
That was an excellent answer.

455
00:31:38,634 --> 00:31:39,734
All right.

456
00:31:39,934 --> 00:31:42,234
Are you now more willing...

457
00:31:42,567 --> 00:31:43,846
...to change?

458
00:31:43,934 --> 00:31:45,177
Not exactly,

459
00:31:46,296 --> 00:31:47,496
but I find it uncomfortable.

460
00:31:48,367 --> 00:31:49,667
These days, especially.

461
00:31:50,167 --> 00:31:52,367
The fact that I'm different from others...

462
00:31:54,267 --> 00:31:55,868
...felt like being a nuisance.

463
00:31:58,901 --> 00:32:00,835
I've never felt like this before.

464
00:32:01,667 --> 00:32:02,767
And what's the reason?

465
00:32:04,100 --> 00:32:06,713
You've been fine with your lifestyle...

466
00:32:06,801 --> 00:32:08,168
...all these years.

467
00:32:08,839 --> 00:32:11,195
Why are you suddenly
uncomfortable with it?

468
00:32:11,284 --> 00:32:12,631
That's what I'm asking.

469
00:32:19,094 --> 00:32:20,695
It's because of Gil O Sol.

470
00:32:22,767 --> 00:32:25,668
I want to change for her.

471
00:32:26,868 --> 00:32:28,502
There are many things...

472
00:32:31,200 --> 00:32:32,567
...I want to do with her.

473
00:32:36,968 --> 00:32:38,302
It's a good change.

474
00:32:39,400 --> 00:32:41,001
Regardless of the reason,

475
00:32:41,534 --> 00:32:43,701
you're finally willing to change.

476
00:32:48,601 --> 00:32:49,968
Then can I...

477
00:32:50,734 --> 00:32:52,668
...go ahead and assume...

478
00:32:52,946 --> 00:32:55,780
...that you're mentally ready
to do anything and everything...

479
00:32:56,133 --> 00:32:57,734
...I ask you to do?

480
00:32:59,567 --> 00:33:01,168
"Anything and everything"?

481
00:33:01,701 --> 00:33:02,768
That's right.

482
00:33:06,234 --> 00:33:07,301
Well...

483
00:33:09,901 --> 00:33:11,502
-Sure.
-Okay!

484
00:33:12,067 --> 00:33:15,768
Then starting today, we shall
work on fixing your problem.

485
00:33:23,534 --> 00:33:25,513
Can you please get rid
of this plastic cover?

486
00:33:25,601 --> 00:33:26,945
It's uncomfortable,

487
00:33:27,033 --> 00:33:28,880
and this sound really gets on my nerves.

488
00:33:28,968 --> 00:33:31,646
No, no way. Don't remove it.
Don't you dare. You can't.

489
00:33:31,734 --> 00:33:34,968
Didn't you say you need my help?
You have the wrong attitude.

490
00:33:35,167 --> 00:33:38,246
By the way, where are we going now?

491
00:33:38,334 --> 00:33:40,701
I'm taking you to...

492
00:33:41,400 --> 00:33:42,700
How shall I describe it?

493
00:33:43,000 --> 00:33:46,434
It's a little trip
for your cognitive behavioral therapy.

494
00:33:46,801 --> 00:33:47,868
A trip?

495
00:33:48,434 --> 00:33:51,668
We can also call it "training".

496
00:34:03,000 --> 00:34:06,112
You don't need to help me.
Just go to work.

497
00:34:06,200 --> 00:34:07,233
It's fine.

498
00:34:07,434 --> 00:34:09,813
I'm done. Look.

499
00:34:09,901 --> 00:34:10,959
Isn't it so clean?

500
00:34:11,467 --> 00:34:14,301
I was the ace of my team
back at Cleaning Fairy.

501
00:34:14,400 --> 00:34:15,767
Ace, my foot.

502
00:34:16,300 --> 00:34:18,012
The owner of this car is very fussy.

503
00:34:18,100 --> 00:34:20,601
He'll complain even if
there's a tiny bit of dust left...

504
00:34:23,367 --> 00:34:25,034
Oh, my goodness.

505
00:34:25,434 --> 00:34:27,846
You're thorough because you take after me.

506
00:34:27,934 --> 00:34:28,934
We're done with this car.

507
00:34:29,300 --> 00:34:30,279
What else can I clean?

508
00:34:30,367 --> 00:34:31,667
We're done for the day.

509
00:34:32,200 --> 00:34:33,038
Already?

510
00:34:33,968 --> 00:34:36,713
Since we're done early,
how about we go for a bowl of udon?

511
00:34:36,801 --> 00:34:40,468
Goodness, I knew that was your goal
when you volunteered to help me.

512
00:34:42,400 --> 00:34:44,234
-How about this?
-Of course. Let's go.

513
00:34:49,901 --> 00:34:52,735
This place looks a lot more romantic
than the photos I saw online.

514
00:34:55,901 --> 00:34:56,934
Baby.

515
00:34:57,701 --> 00:35:00,901
Are we going to sleep
together here tonight?

516
00:35:06,000 --> 00:35:09,467
What? Sleep together? Here?

517
00:35:10,100 --> 00:35:11,546
What? Why?

518
00:35:11,634 --> 00:35:13,235
Why would we sleep here?

519
00:35:13,634 --> 00:35:14,901
Hey, stop!

520
00:35:15,868 --> 00:35:16,868
Stop right there!

521
00:35:18,734 --> 00:35:21,912
Why did you clean your room?
It's not your mom's death anniversary.

522
00:35:22,000 --> 00:35:25,701
Oh, I just thought it looked untidy.

523
00:35:26,400 --> 00:35:28,767
I haven't been cleaning regularly,

524
00:35:28,868 --> 00:35:30,646
saying I'm always tired and busy.

525
00:35:30,734 --> 00:35:32,079
I don't want to be like that anymore.

526
00:35:32,167 --> 00:35:34,367
I'm going to keep things tidy
and stop putting things off.

527
00:35:34,501 --> 00:35:36,102
That's why I cleaned my room.

528
00:35:41,334 --> 00:35:43,968
Do you like that guy that much?

529
00:35:44,467 --> 00:35:46,379
-What?
-You never listened to me...

530
00:35:46,467 --> 00:35:47,801
...when I nagged you about it.

531
00:35:47,901 --> 00:35:49,802
But you've totally changed
since you started dating him.

532
00:35:51,234 --> 00:35:54,267
That's not what it is.
Don't be silly, Dad.

533
00:35:54,367 --> 00:35:57,112
Whatever. Then why are
your ears all red now?

534
00:35:57,200 --> 00:35:58,467
Don't lie to my face.

535
00:36:02,567 --> 00:36:03,634
This change...

536
00:36:03,868 --> 00:36:05,602
...makes me happy.

537
00:36:06,133 --> 00:36:07,834
It gives me a relief.

538
00:36:13,300 --> 00:36:14,901
So what's your plan now?

539
00:36:15,334 --> 00:36:16,835
I mean, you quit your job.

540
00:36:17,234 --> 00:36:18,501
You must have a plan.

541
00:36:21,133 --> 00:36:22,579
For the time being,

542
00:36:22,667 --> 00:36:24,767
I want to help you like I did today.

543
00:36:24,968 --> 00:36:26,936
I'm not saying I won't
do anything productive.

544
00:36:27,434 --> 00:36:29,035
I want to take some time...

545
00:36:29,300 --> 00:36:32,667
...and figure out
what I really want to do.

546
00:36:34,901 --> 00:36:36,502
Since I quit hurdling,

547
00:36:37,267 --> 00:36:39,501
I haven't had a chance to
sit down and think about,

548
00:36:39,934 --> 00:36:42,201
what I really want to do.

549
00:36:45,133 --> 00:36:48,413
"I don't care what the job is.
I just want to get a job..."

550
00:36:48,501 --> 00:36:50,002
"...so I can make enough money..."

551
00:36:50,467 --> 00:36:52,467
"...to lead a decent life."

552
00:36:52,801 --> 00:36:54,235
That's what I thought.

553
00:36:56,400 --> 00:36:58,101
But I don't want to
live like that anymore.

554
00:36:59,701 --> 00:37:02,001
I want to find out what I really like...

555
00:37:02,200 --> 00:37:04,467
...and what I want to do...

556
00:37:05,200 --> 00:37:07,767
...so I can enjoy my life.

557
00:37:08,467 --> 00:37:11,268
That's why I want to
take the proper path...

558
00:37:12,934 --> 00:37:14,635
...even though it may take longer.

559
00:37:16,133 --> 00:37:17,200
I see.

560
00:37:19,801 --> 00:37:21,801
If your mom heard that,
she'd be so happy for you.

561
00:37:26,067 --> 00:37:28,100
The problem with O Dol
has been resolved too.

562
00:37:28,234 --> 00:37:30,701
Don't you feel like it
was a gift from Mom?

563
00:37:33,033 --> 00:37:34,534
I miss her so much.

564
00:37:43,901 --> 00:37:47,468
By the way, why did you visit Mom alone?

565
00:37:47,734 --> 00:37:49,001
We could've come with you.

566
00:37:49,501 --> 00:37:50,501
What?

567
00:37:50,701 --> 00:37:53,846
Aren't you the one who left
the yogurt and the flowers?

568
00:37:53,934 --> 00:37:55,246
What are you talking about?

569
00:37:55,334 --> 00:37:58,202
I've been very busy, so I
haven't had time to visit her.

570
00:37:59,300 --> 00:38:02,646
Speaking of which, I
should visit her soon.

571
00:38:02,734 --> 00:38:05,134
I feel like I've been neglecting her.

572
00:38:13,267 --> 00:38:14,400
Go away, bugs!

573
00:38:17,133 --> 00:38:19,067
It's freezing. What are we doing now?

574
00:38:20,767 --> 00:38:22,668
Let's go home.

575
00:38:23,467 --> 00:38:25,934
You said you want to change for O Sol.

576
00:38:26,234 --> 00:38:28,513
Is this the extent of your love?

577
00:38:28,601 --> 00:38:31,202
Gosh, you're one petty quack.

578
00:38:32,167 --> 00:38:33,701
So? What now?

579
00:38:34,400 --> 00:38:35,901
What should I do?

580
00:38:37,033 --> 00:38:38,233
I'm relieved...

581
00:38:38,634 --> 00:38:42,001
...because you actually
seem like a nice guy.

582
00:38:43,901 --> 00:38:44,880
Are you realizing it just now?

583
00:38:44,968 --> 00:38:46,702
You're confident that you
won't make me regret...

584
00:38:48,367 --> 00:38:49,801
...giving up on O Sol, right?

585
00:38:51,200 --> 00:38:52,600
What are you talking about?

586
00:38:52,834 --> 00:38:54,967
Please protect O Sol...

587
00:38:55,567 --> 00:38:57,001
...no matter what.

588
00:38:58,467 --> 00:39:01,801
I think all will be fine
if you don't give up.

589
00:39:04,067 --> 00:39:07,579
Well, I don't think that's
any of your business.

590
00:39:07,667 --> 00:39:10,101
I will never give up.

591
00:39:10,834 --> 00:39:14,001
I'll be sure to protect O Sol
and keep her safe at all times.

592
00:39:15,534 --> 00:39:17,468
That's why I'm here now.

593
00:39:18,801 --> 00:39:19,868
And?

594
00:39:20,567 --> 00:39:22,168
Are you enjoying it?

595
00:39:24,801 --> 00:39:25,801
Not really.

596
00:39:27,367 --> 00:39:28,634
But I should still do it.

597
00:39:31,567 --> 00:39:32,767
I will do it.

598
00:39:33,667 --> 00:39:34,734
Now,

599
00:39:36,067 --> 00:39:37,067
I must.

600
00:39:45,767 --> 00:39:46,867
So?

601
00:39:48,400 --> 00:39:51,433
Where's the list of
the disciplinary committee members?

602
00:39:52,400 --> 00:39:55,834
There's actually something
I need to tell you, sir.

603
00:39:57,234 --> 00:39:58,334
Go ahead.

604
00:39:59,622 --> 00:40:00,755
I don't think...

605
00:40:01,767 --> 00:40:04,034
...I can work for you anymore.

606
00:40:06,234 --> 00:40:08,880
I no longer want to do things that
Mr. Jang doesn't want.

607
00:40:08,968 --> 00:40:10,168
Things...

608
00:40:10,667 --> 00:40:11,700
...that he doesn't want?

609
00:40:12,234 --> 00:40:15,168
Stop meddling in everything,
including the disciplinary hearing.

610
00:40:16,133 --> 00:40:17,567
I kindly ask you...

611
00:40:18,033 --> 00:40:19,967
...to stop giving Ms. Gil's
family a hard time.

612
00:40:21,701 --> 00:40:24,669
She left the company voluntarily,
so I think...

613
00:40:25,100 --> 00:40:27,434
...you should leave her alone.

614
00:40:30,732 --> 00:40:32,559
Seon Gyeol is...

615
00:40:33,868 --> 00:40:36,702
...going out with that girl, I hear.

616
00:40:36,868 --> 00:40:38,168
It's between the two of them.

617
00:40:38,934 --> 00:40:40,967
It's none of your business.

618
00:40:41,868 --> 00:40:45,346
Why did you never tell me her mom died...

619
00:40:45,434 --> 00:40:47,734
...in the Jungang-dong accident?

620
00:40:50,634 --> 00:40:53,868
I'll protect Seon Gyeol...

621
00:40:54,067 --> 00:40:55,534
...in my own way.

622
00:40:56,278 --> 00:40:57,155
All right.

623
00:40:58,437 --> 00:41:00,089
Thank you for all your help so far.

624
00:41:09,100 --> 00:41:10,968
The disciplinary committee
will be held tomorrow, right?

625
00:41:12,634 --> 00:41:14,568
Don't be nervous. It'll be all right.

626
00:41:15,534 --> 00:41:16,901
You came to say that?

627
00:41:18,534 --> 00:41:19,667
No.

628
00:41:21,868 --> 00:41:23,035
Take it back.

629
00:41:29,701 --> 00:41:31,535
The first medal you win...

630
00:41:31,767 --> 00:41:33,668
...after the disciplinary committee.

631
00:41:35,100 --> 00:41:36,200
I want that.

632
00:41:37,534 --> 00:41:39,312
You know how I am, right?

633
00:41:39,400 --> 00:41:41,045
I'll only accept a gold medal.

634
00:41:41,133 --> 00:41:42,734
You better work hard.

635
00:41:42,901 --> 00:41:45,968
Are you serious?

636
00:41:46,367 --> 00:41:47,579
Do you really mean it?

637
00:41:47,667 --> 00:41:51,501
If I win a gold medal,
you'll go out with me?

638
00:41:51,834 --> 00:41:54,134
We'll see.

639
00:41:55,901 --> 00:41:57,001
Guys!

640
00:41:58,868 --> 00:42:00,268
Let's go!

641
00:42:02,501 --> 00:42:04,768
I'll win a gold medal!

642
00:42:17,567 --> 00:42:18,767
Come to the window.

643
00:42:37,634 --> 00:42:44,135
(I love you, O Sol.)

644
00:42:46,100 --> 00:42:48,500
(I love you, O Sol.)

645
00:42:50,234 --> 00:42:52,068
(You're the only one. You're so pretty.)

646
00:42:52,167 --> 00:42:53,646
(Look at me only. Let's walk together.)

647
00:42:53,734 --> 00:42:54,934
(We'll always be together.)

648
00:43:01,367 --> 00:43:02,467
Hello.

649
00:43:02,868 --> 00:43:04,068
What's going on?

650
00:43:08,167 --> 00:43:09,300
Hold on.

651
00:43:12,667 --> 00:43:14,168
Are you outside?

652
00:43:14,801 --> 00:43:15,868
No.

653
00:43:16,934 --> 00:43:18,234
I'm right in front of you.

654
00:43:22,834 --> 00:43:24,768
How did you come in?

655
00:43:25,234 --> 00:43:26,367
Where are your gloves?

656
00:43:27,467 --> 00:43:29,068
I opened the doors with bare hands.

657
00:43:29,834 --> 00:43:32,101
-I did some special training.
-Special training?

658
00:43:34,167 --> 00:43:35,167
Are you okay?

659
00:43:42,167 --> 00:43:43,901
I thought I'd be okay,

660
00:43:45,167 --> 00:43:46,668
but I'm not.

661
00:43:47,767 --> 00:43:50,167
I think I have to go out.

662
00:43:53,601 --> 00:43:54,734
Come.

663
00:44:08,501 --> 00:44:09,634
"Gil O Sol".

664
00:44:16,767 --> 00:44:19,034
I'll go wash my hands now.

665
00:44:24,334 --> 00:44:26,001
I'm proud of you.

666
00:44:28,501 --> 00:44:31,168
Maybe I'll stay a bit longer.

667
00:45:57,701 --> 00:46:00,768
Thank you for the security camera footage.

668
00:46:04,934 --> 00:46:06,101
I'm sorry...

669
00:46:06,200 --> 00:46:09,212
...that's the only thing I can do for you.

670
00:46:09,300 --> 00:46:11,067
I've always wanted to ask you this.

671
00:46:11,834 --> 00:46:13,834
What's the relationship
between you and Chairman Cha?

672
00:46:14,934 --> 00:46:17,902
I don't understand
why you would have wanted...

673
00:46:18,167 --> 00:46:19,868
...to help him.

674
00:46:20,234 --> 00:46:23,534
You've also been actively involved
with Seon Gyeol's surroundings.

675
00:46:23,834 --> 00:46:25,834
Was that also for Chairman Cha's sake?

676
00:46:27,534 --> 00:46:28,449
No.

677
00:46:28,804 --> 00:46:30,556
It wasn't for his sake.

678
00:46:31,767 --> 00:46:33,167
It was for my own sake.

679
00:46:33,767 --> 00:46:37,834
To me, Mr. Jang meant my son's future.

680
00:46:40,934 --> 00:46:43,468
I did the things I did to make
Mr. Jang happy.

681
00:46:44,167 --> 00:46:45,934
But my judgment was wrong.

682
00:46:46,400 --> 00:46:48,134
I only made things harder for him.

683
00:46:50,868 --> 00:46:53,012
By the way, tomorrow's
disciplinary committee...

684
00:46:53,100 --> 00:46:54,780
...might not go very well.

685
00:46:54,868 --> 00:46:56,569
Why do you say that?

686
00:46:56,667 --> 00:47:00,401
Chairman Cha found out about O Sol.

687
00:47:00,901 --> 00:47:04,502
Even the fact that her mom died
in the Jungang-dong accident.

688
00:47:05,100 --> 00:47:06,500
It seems like...

689
00:47:07,534 --> 00:47:11,035
...he has decided to break up
Mr. Jang and O Sol.

690
00:47:11,539 --> 00:47:12,783
To do that,

691
00:47:13,628 --> 00:47:15,489
he will use O Sol's family.

692
00:47:24,434 --> 00:47:26,734
I'm Mr. Jang Seon Gyeol's doctor,
Choi Ha In.

693
00:47:28,734 --> 00:47:31,235
Can I have a word with you, Chairman Cha?

694
00:47:37,416 --> 00:47:39,730
So you have three months left at the most.

695
00:47:41,167 --> 00:47:42,968
And you haven't even told your family.

696
00:47:44,300 --> 00:47:48,442
If it gets out before the heir is decided,

697
00:47:49,334 --> 00:47:51,868
AG Group will suffer immensely.

698
00:47:53,634 --> 00:47:56,667
Are you blackmailing me?

699
00:47:57,834 --> 00:48:01,702
Yes, it's just what you think it is.

700
00:48:02,434 --> 00:48:03,567
I'm blackmailing you.

701
00:48:03,734 --> 00:48:06,001
So what do you want?

702
00:48:07,501 --> 00:48:09,402
You must have come to me...

703
00:48:09,767 --> 00:48:11,401
...because there is something you want.

704
00:48:11,760 --> 00:48:15,127
Leave O Sol's family alone.

705
00:48:16,734 --> 00:48:19,702
When AG Group was redeveloping
Jungang-dong six years ago...

706
00:48:20,734 --> 00:48:22,535
...your misjudgment...

707
00:48:23,267 --> 00:48:25,300
...resulted in four casualties.

708
00:48:26,234 --> 00:48:27,835
And I hear you're aware...

709
00:48:28,968 --> 00:48:31,936
...that one of them is O Sol's mother.

710
00:48:33,200 --> 00:48:36,068
Instead of apologizing
to the victims and their families,

711
00:48:37,300 --> 00:48:39,433
you want to trample on
them for the second time?

712
00:48:40,334 --> 00:48:41,701
To stop you,

713
00:48:42,501 --> 00:48:44,634
I'd do something even
worse than blackmailing.

714
00:48:57,109 --> 00:48:59,308
The disciplinary committee
is today, right?

715
00:48:59,397 --> 00:49:02,331
Yes. But the result is already decided.

716
00:49:02,934 --> 00:49:04,967
-I'm not so worried.
-That's good.

717
00:49:06,067 --> 00:49:09,935
Do you want to come
to my place after work?

718
00:49:10,968 --> 00:49:12,135
We should celebrate.

719
00:49:13,501 --> 00:49:14,701
That's unnecessary.

720
00:49:15,467 --> 00:49:16,320
Should we get a cake?

721
00:49:16,736 --> 00:49:18,089
Should we cook something nice?

722
00:49:20,567 --> 00:49:21,567
It's raining.

723
00:49:22,200 --> 00:49:23,446
I hung the laundry outside.

724
00:49:23,534 --> 00:49:25,468
I'm sorry, I'll call you later.

725
00:49:35,167 --> 00:49:36,300
I took care of it for you.

726
00:49:45,400 --> 00:49:46,600
Thank you.

727
00:49:49,000 --> 00:49:51,434
I thought you went to O Dol's
disciplinary committee.

728
00:49:52,767 --> 00:49:55,268
He threw a fit, saying there
was no need for me to go.

729
00:49:56,033 --> 00:49:57,767
I wonder how it's going.

730
00:49:59,067 --> 00:50:02,834
I'm glad O Dol can start
his training again.

731
00:50:08,734 --> 00:50:11,635
About those receipts...

732
00:50:12,200 --> 00:50:13,701
The ones you said my dad left behind.

733
00:50:13,801 --> 00:50:14,801
Yes.

734
00:50:14,901 --> 00:50:16,968
My dad said he never went there.

735
00:50:22,247 --> 00:50:25,048
Is there something you are hiding from me?

736
00:50:26,267 --> 00:50:28,079
No, I'm not hiding anything.

737
00:50:28,167 --> 00:50:29,200
By any chance,

738
00:50:31,667 --> 00:50:33,334
are you...

739
00:50:35,334 --> 00:50:37,801
...the one who leaves yogurt behind...

740
00:50:38,100 --> 00:50:40,367
...for me?

741
00:50:48,033 --> 00:50:48,913
Yes.

742
00:50:50,339 --> 00:50:51,372
You're right.

743
00:50:52,400 --> 00:50:55,034
It's me who left the yogurt.

744
00:50:57,000 --> 00:50:58,234
Really?

745
00:51:00,601 --> 00:51:01,601
Why?

746
00:51:02,067 --> 00:51:03,234
A long time ago,

747
00:51:04,501 --> 00:51:06,968
there was a time you gave me yogurt once.

748
00:51:10,200 --> 00:51:12,434
Here. Drink this.

749
00:51:20,400 --> 00:51:22,034
Drink it when it's still cold.

750
00:51:25,267 --> 00:51:26,701
That yogurt...

751
00:51:27,234 --> 00:51:28,868
...provided me with solace too.

752
00:51:30,267 --> 00:51:32,300
I received solace...

753
00:51:33,367 --> 00:51:34,968
...but you didn't.

754
00:51:36,758 --> 00:51:37,652
That's why.

755
00:51:39,679 --> 00:51:41,180
From that moment on,

756
00:51:41,701 --> 00:51:44,302
you and your family
were always on my mind.

757
00:51:46,367 --> 00:51:47,868
I want to stay with Mr. Gil,

758
00:51:48,667 --> 00:51:49,934
you, and O Dol.

759
00:51:51,701 --> 00:51:53,402
I know I won't be much help,

760
00:51:54,267 --> 00:51:55,868
but can I stay here like this?

761
00:51:56,800 --> 00:51:58,267
If you allow me to,

762
00:51:59,133 --> 00:52:00,533
I want to help.

763
00:52:01,501 --> 00:52:02,634
No matter what it is.

764
00:52:15,133 --> 00:52:16,479
(Disciplinary Committee)

765
00:52:16,567 --> 00:52:18,801
We hereby give Gil O Dol
of the taekwondo club...

766
00:52:19,234 --> 00:52:21,035
...of Dong Myeong High School...

767
00:52:23,000 --> 00:52:25,267
...a one-year suspension
from practicing taekwondo.

768
00:52:28,033 --> 00:52:29,033
What?

769
00:52:29,300 --> 00:52:30,713
What? One year?

770
00:52:30,801 --> 00:52:32,279
I think there's been a mistake.

771
00:52:32,367 --> 00:52:34,834
You saw that it was
an act of self-defense.

772
00:52:35,200 --> 00:52:37,233
Sir... Sir!

773
00:52:53,133 --> 00:52:55,300
I'm sure there's been a mistake.

774
00:52:55,801 --> 00:52:57,613
I'll talk to the coach...

775
00:52:57,701 --> 00:52:59,935
...and find out what's happening...

776
00:53:00,033 --> 00:53:02,367
-...so don't worry...
-About O Dol's disciplinary action.

777
00:53:02,534 --> 00:53:04,135
Isn't it a bit too harsh?

778
00:53:04,367 --> 00:53:07,279
What's his relationship with AG Group?

779
00:53:07,377 --> 00:53:08,544
Didn't you hear?

780
00:53:08,868 --> 00:53:12,102
There's a rumor his sister is
dating the grandson of AG Group.

781
00:53:12,767 --> 00:53:13,867
Is that true?

782
00:53:14,000 --> 00:53:15,012
You didn't know?

783
00:53:15,100 --> 00:53:16,267
What did you just say?

784
00:53:16,519 --> 00:53:17,423
"AG Group"?

785
00:53:17,512 --> 00:53:18,912
-O Dol.
-You just said AG.

786
00:53:18,983 --> 00:53:20,546
What are you talking about?

787
00:53:20,634 --> 00:53:22,179
I'm sorry.

788
00:53:22,267 --> 00:53:24,068
Hey. Mister.

789
00:53:26,567 --> 00:53:28,134
Dad, what were they talking about?

790
00:53:53,767 --> 00:53:55,701
I received solace...

791
00:53:57,801 --> 00:53:59,302
...but you didn't.

792
00:54:29,534 --> 00:54:31,212
You're back. How did it go?

793
00:54:31,300 --> 00:54:32,700
Can you continue your training?

794
00:54:37,100 --> 00:54:38,734
Why are you all wet?

795
00:54:41,667 --> 00:54:42,679
What?

796
00:54:42,919 --> 00:54:44,219
Did something go wrong?

797
00:54:55,805 --> 00:54:56,805
Dad.

798
00:54:58,187 --> 00:54:59,521
Why him?

799
00:55:02,400 --> 00:55:03,945
What do you mean?

800
00:55:04,033 --> 00:55:05,734
Why that jerk?

801
00:55:08,667 --> 00:55:11,809
Didn't you know
he's the grandson of AG Group?

802
00:55:13,167 --> 00:55:14,668
Why that jerk?

803
00:55:15,633 --> 00:55:16,766
Why him of all people?

804
00:55:17,249 --> 00:55:19,461
Why must you date a guy from the family...

805
00:55:19,550 --> 00:55:21,451
...that killed your mom? Why?

806
00:55:25,275 --> 00:55:27,068
AG? What do you mean?

807
00:55:28,466 --> 00:55:30,766
Mr. Jang is...

